channel.title: Everytime i pickup d claws it comes up as pieces of eight?
channel.description: i have just downloaded chris-scape v1. Its is a 317 type of server. Since i had trouble using i client i use client.silabsoft.org. when i log in is says to do ::dclaws for d claws. so i do it. instead it gives me pieces of eight. so i go an check in the items.cfg and i find the code for dragon claws, i go back into the game and i do ::pickup (code for drag claws) (quantity) and it still gives me pieces of eight. If anyone could tell me how to solve this problem it would be great!

item.title: Everytime i pickup d claws it comes up as pieces of eight?
item.dc:creator: @dillingo dillingo
item.description:
@dillingo wrote:

D claws, and many other new rs items don’t work on silab. You NEED to download a different client if you want to see them/use them.

item.title: Everytime i pickup d claws it comes up as pieces of eight?
item.dc:creator: @noobie22 Noobie22
item.description:
@noobie22 wrote:

  1. Wrong section, hit the models section.

  2. You either have the wrong ints, or models. If you have the models, put .rar(or 7zip) files into the models folder for your client.

  3. Try it.

item.title: Everytime i pickup d claws it comes up as pieces of eight?
item.dc:creator: @gunz4life gunz4life
item.description:
@gunz4life wrote:

If you do ::dclaws and comes up as a “eight” either, you don’t have the items model added into the client, or you add the wrong id.
